+# Simplified Product-Attribute Relationships
+
+This module implements a simplified approach to product-attribute relationships compared to the original complex structure in Saleor.
+
+## Original Complexity
+
+The original implementation used multiple models for managing product-attribute relationships:
+- `AttributeProduct` - links attributes to product types
+- `AssignedProductAttribute` - links product types to specific products  
+- `AssignedProductAttributeValue` - links assigned attributes to specific values
+- Similar structures for variants
+
+This created a complex web of relationships that made queries and maintenance more difficult.
+
+## Simplified Approach
+
+Our simplified approach reduces this to three core models:
+1. `ProductAttributeAssignment` - Links products to their assigned attributes and values
+2. `VariantAttributeAssignment` - Links product variants to their assigned attributes and values  
+3. `ProductTypeAttributeAssignment` - Links product types to their available attributes
+
+## Benefits
+
+- Fewer models to maintain and understand
+- Simpler queries for retrieving product attributes
+- Easier to extend and modify
+- More intuitive relationship structure
+
+## Usage
+
+The simplified models maintain compatibility with existing code through the same interface methods:
+- `Product.get_attribute_values()` - Get all attribute values for a product
+- `Product.get_attributes()` - Get all attributes for a product
+- `ProductVariant.get_attribute_values()` - Get all attribute values for a variant
